Beker Industries Corp said itwas unable to confirm its plan for reorganization at a March 5hearing before the U.S. Bankruptcy Court because necessaryagreements had not been reached with its institutional lenders.    The company said it could set no specific date forcompleting its reorganization.    At the March 5 hearing, the company said it filed a motionfor approval of an agreement that has been reached in principalwith a unit of Freeport-McMoRan Inc &lt;FTX> for the sale ofBeker's facilities in Louisiana and Florida. Reuter&#3;